author: @BoP
text: The real meta game is guessing who is the culprit based on overarching events + member personalities. See they wouldn't pick Jihyo or Momo because of them being in the news a lot. They wouldn't pick Jeongyeon because she had a leave of absence. DaChaeTzu are the youngest so they wouldn't do that either. Nayeon is too obvious and they wouldn't tarnish Sana's bubbly persona. So it's gotta be Mina. They are gonna play into her mysterious and quiet side. Notice how they didn't give her a lot of screen time this episode. They are trying to make us forget about her character so it surprises us. I believe it's Mina.

author: @kshinichi2637
text:
Dahyun -She watches a lot Murd3r/Cri*me movies . She must've learned a lot of tricks after watching lots of Murd*r/Crime movies. The song title and what happened to Na Gasu is too coincidental, like it's planned beforehand, and her research about how the sales of the songs of the famous artists who dies goes up made it looked a lot more like it was really planned.

CEO Im -She said Na Gasu was the only artist in her company. But why is the company in such a huge deficit? Na Gasu was on a hiatus for years y'know. Does Na Gasu have something to do with the company being in that state? Does CEO Im loathe Na Gasu because of it. -Also, it's questionable why Na Gasu is her only artist. Maybe she's that obsessive freak that did something to Na Gasu who only wants Na Gasu for herself. If so, then the reason she murder*d Na Gasu must be because the huge problem Na Gasu made for the company and Na Gasu dating Momo (Momo said she and Na Gasu went out) 

President Park (Jihyo) -There are too many hints that leads to her. Like it was meant to mislead others. It's like the perpetrator knows that she's a big fan of Na Gasu and that she's a pharmacist. It's like the perpetrator wants to take adv4ntage of this. 

Showcase Director, Sana -I don't think it's Sana. As she said, they've spent nights and tired themselves for this showcase. And her, arguing with Na Gasu because of Na Gasu's opinion for the showcase just shows she is passionate/determined for the showcase. She wouldn't give so much effort for the showcase if she would just murd*r him in the end. If she is the perpetrator, she wouldn't mind arguing with Na Gasu. She would just let him be, take his opinions or what, because in the end, she will just murd*r him before the showcase starts.

Welp, this is only my opinion. How 'bout you? Who do you think is it?
